      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need some help with a professional email. I'm an HR manager at a logistics company and I have to write a formal reprimand to an employee. They've been about 15 minutes late to every shift for the last two weeks. I need it to be firm and professional but not like, unnecessarily aggressive. Can you draft something for me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! Here's a draft for your professional email:\n\n---\n\nSubject: Urgent: Addressing Attendance Concerns\n\nDear [Employee's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to address a matter of concern regarding your attendance at work. Over the past two weeks, it has come to our attention that you have been arriving approximately 15 minutes late to each shift. While we understand that unforeseen circumstances can occasionally cause delays, consistent tardiness is not acceptable and impacts the overall efficiency of our team.\n\nAs an HR manager, I must emphasize the importance of punctuality in maintaining a productive work environment. We rely on each team member to contribute their time and effort effectively, and your consistent lateness is disrupting this balance. To ensure that we can address this issue constructively, I would like to schedule a meeting with you to discuss the underlying reasons for your tardiness and explore potential solutions.\n\nPlease understand that this is a formal reprimand, and we expect immediate improvement in your punctuality. If we do not see a positive change, we may need to consider further actions to ensure the smooth operation of our logistics services.\n\nThank you for your attention to this matter. I look forward to discussing this with you soon.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[",
